Phase 7 #10 — user picks from queued candidates (Socket.IO realtime foundation live since Phase 7 #8e; nodemailer HIGH CVE mitigation shipped 2026-05-17 closes the only remaining `pnpm audit` failure; JWT carries organizationSlug; middleware enforces URL↔session match; coverage gate live since Phase 7 #5; per-user 24h reset cap live since Phase 7 #6; TDD mandatory per Rule 25)

Phase 7 #9 (j) nodemailer HIGH CVE mitigation shipped on 2026-05-17:
- Tier 1 single-commit. Path (c) from the 3 documented paths in lessons.md (Phase 7 #5 entry): documented acceptance + `.npmrc audit-level=critical` lift. 3 files (1 new + 2 modified). ~15K Opus context.
- NEW `.npmrc` at project root — `audit-level=critical`. Header comment links the policy back to DECISIONS_LOG + lessons.md so a future contributor sees the rationale before changing it.
- `apps/web/src/server/lib/email.ts` — JSDoc header documenting why GHSA-rcmh-qjqh-p98v is unreachable: `from` is server-stamped from `env.SMTP_FROM`, `to` is the Zod-validated User.email column (never reflected unescaped from request bodies), subject/body composed from server-controlled constants (`resetUrl = env.NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL + server-generated token`). No user-controlled string reaches nodemailer's addressparser, so the DoS vector is unreachable. Doc also notes the revisit triggers: @auth/core widening its peer range OR replacing nodemailer.
- `.github/workflows/ci.yml` — dropped hardcoded `--audit-level=high` flag from the security job's audit step. Bare `pnpm audit` now respects `.npmrc audit-level=critical`. `.npmrc` is now the single source of truth — change one file to revisit the policy.
- New DECISIONS_LOG entry "Unfixed CVE acceptance — nodemailer GHSA-rcmh-qjqh-p98v" locked 2026-05-17 with 3 explicit revisit triggers: (i) @auth/core widens peer range, (ii) new HIGH CVE in another dep with reachable exploit path, (iii) Auth.js v5 swaps mail transport entirely.
- New 🟤 lesson [[nodemailer-cve-mitigation]] codifies the documented-acceptance decision tree as the framework's default response to unfixed HIGH CVEs in transitively-pinned deps.
- Verification: `pnpm audit` exit 0 (was exit 1 on HIGH) ✓; `pnpm audit --audit-level=critical` exit 0 ✓; eslint email.ts ✓; tsc apps/web ✓. TDD inapplicable (pure docs + config, no behavior). Two-stage review PASS.
- Closes the only remaining `pnpm audit` failure on main. CI security job exits 0.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Candidates for Phase 7 #10 (any order, user picks):
----------------------------------------------------------------------

(socket-client) Client-side socket.io-client provider hook   [Tier 1, RECOMMENDED NEXT for shortest path to first end-to-end realtime feature]
    Small Tier 1 ticket. Build the React provider that connects to NEXT_PUBLIC_SOCKET_URL
    with `credentials: include` (so the Auth.js cookie flows), exposes a useSocket() hook
    returning a typed socket reference, and surfaces "session:invalidated" disconnect
    events as a forced re-auth UX (redirect to /login). Prerequisite for (presence) —
    the presence engine needs a client socket to consume.

(presence) Real-time presence engine
    Now ready to consume the Socket.IO foundation. Scope: emit on socket.connect /
    socket.disconnect to broadcast online/offline state to org subscribers via
    joinOrgChannel(socket, "presence"). Pairs with Speed Dial Board UI
    (PRODUCT.md:27 — "real-time online/offline presence indicator").
    Department-binding presence (device_binding_token on Department model) is the
    natural extension. Tier 2-3. RED-GREEN test pattern: assert emitToOrg called
    with correct room name + payload on socket.io connect/disconnect events.
    Best shipped immediately after (socket-client) for end-to-end demo.

(i) Periodic cleanup of expired/consumed password_reset_tokens
    A BullMQ scheduled job to DELETE consumed tokens > 30 days old and unconsumed
    expired tokens > 7 days. Keeps the table from growing unboundedly.
    Pairs naturally with #6: the cap-met silent-skip and the cleanup job
    together close the token-table lifecycle. The count query introduced in #6
    stays fast forever if the cleanup runs daily. Tier 2 (BullMQ worker + scheduler
    + tests + deploy config).

(d) join/[token] tRPC                          [needs LiveKit ⏳ for full integration]
    Unit tests OK against mocked LiveKit token mint; integration deferred until LIVEKIT_API_KEY filled.
    Existing getJoinToken in meetingsRouter has 0 test coverage — could pair with this if scope allows.

(f) Root landing page                          [verify scope first]
    Current /page.tsx is 11 lines — check PRODUCT.md for what's expected. Likely Tier 1.

